'''2011年基督城地震'''（{{lang-en|Christchurch 2011 earthquake}}），是当地时间2011年2月22日12:51（[[UTC|UTC]]2月21日23:51）发生在[[紐西兰|紐西兰]]第二大城市、[[南岛|南岛]]第一大城市[[基督城|基督城]]附近的一场6.3级地震，震中位于[[利特尔顿|利特尔顿]]以西2公里、[[基督城|基督城]]东南10公里，此后又发生多次余震。因为此次地震震级大、震源深度较浅，且震央位于市中心，所以对当地造成了巨大破坏，损失远远超过了当地[[2010年坎特伯雷地震|2010年9月的7.1级地震]]<ref>{{cite web | language = Zh-hans | publisher = 中国新闻网 | title = 新西兰第二大城市几近毁灭 百年大教堂被毁 | url = http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2011/02-23/2861156.shtml | date = 2011-02-23 | accessdate = 2011-02-23 | archive-date = 2011-03-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110316121308/http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2011/02-23/2861156.shtml | dead-url = no }}</ref>。截至当地时间2月26日下午5点51分已确认145人死亡，超过200人失踪<ref name="current death toll">{{cite web|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/national/christchurch-earthquake/4707095/Earthquake-death-toll-rises-to-145|title=Earthquake death toll rises to 145|work=stuff.co.nz|date=2011-02-26|accessdate=2011-02-26|archive-date=2018-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180716055318/http://www.stuff.co.nz/national/christchurch-earthquake/4707095/Earthquake-death-toll-rises-to-145|dead-url=no}}</ref>，使这次地震成为新西兰有史以来死亡人数最多的自然灾害之一。2月22日，新西兰总理[[约翰·基|约翰·基]]称这次地震“可能是新西兰历史上最黑暗的一天”。最終確認共計185人罹難，失踪人口中包括20多个国家的公民。<ref name=NZH-toll>{{cite news|title=Earthquake toll rises to 145|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10708888|accessdate=2011-02-26|newspaper=New Zealand Herald|date=2011-02-26|archive-date=2012-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120117082028/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10708888|dead-url=no}}</ref>新西兰当局首次宣布全国进入紧急状态。[[JP摩根|摩根大通]]的投资分析師预计此次地震将造成保险业损失120亿[[美元|美元]]（160亿[[新西兰元|新西兰元]]）。<ref name="jpmorgan">{{cite web|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/new-zealand-s-earthquake-may-become-costliest-insured-disaster-since-2008.html|title=New Zealand's Earthquake May Become Costliest Insured Disaster Since 2008|author=Noah Buhayar, Jacob Greber and Nichola Saminather|work=Bloomberg|date=2011-02-23|accessdate=2011-02-24|archive-date=2015-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150126130543/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/new-zealand-s-earthquake-may-become-costliest-insured-disaster-since-2008.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==地震概況==
[[File:2011_Canterbury_earthquake_intensity.jpg|thumb]]
此次地震是[[2010年坎特伯雷地震|2010年坎特伯雷地震]]之后的一系列地震和余震之一。美国地质调查局报告和新西兰认为此次地震是上述地震的余震<ref>{{cite web |title=Earthquake Summary |url=http://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/recenteqsww/Quakes/usb0001igm.php#summary |work=Magnitude 6.3 - SOUTH ISLAND OF NEW ZEALAND |publisher=U.S. Geological Survey, National Earthquake Information Center |accessdate=2011-02-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110222135145/http://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/recenteqsww/Quakes/usb0001igm.php#summary |archivedate=2011-02-22 }}</ref>，但部分科学家认为这次地震发生的位置位于另外的断裂带上，因此是一次独立的地震<ref name="Holland">{{cite news | url = http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/christchurch-the-ticking-timebomb/story-fn6b3v4f-1226011617484 | title = Christchurch: The ticking timebomb | author = Holland, Malcolm | work = The Daily Telegraph | publisher = News Limited | location = Australia | date = 2011-02-25 | accessdate = 2011-02-25 | archive-date = 2014-06-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140622084047/http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/christchurch-the-ticking-timebomb/story-fn6b3v4f-1226011617484 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

最初的报告认为震源深度为5公里，但后续分析可能改写这一观点。地震发生于一条此前不为人知的东西向断裂带，长约17千米，深度3-12米。<ref name="Davison25">{{cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10708579|title=Christchurch earthquake: Deadly tremors rebounded on city|author=Davison, Isaac|work=New Zealand Herald|publisher=APN Holdings|date=2011-02-25|accessdate=2011-02-25|archive-date=2020-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002201228/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10708579|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==伤亡及损失情况==
截至2月26日，已确认145人在地震-{}-中死亡，<ref name="current death toll"/>但仅坎特伯里电视台大楼尚有过百人失踪，因此死亡人数可能继续增加<ref name="CTV toll">{{cite news |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10708295 |title=Christchurch quake: More than 100 may have perished in CTV |newspaper=New Zealand Herald |date=2011-02-23 |accessdate=2011-02-26 |archive-date=2020-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929110517/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10708295 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

地震发生当日的当地时间下午5时，新西兰广播电台报道称80%的市区停电，全城供排水系统陷于瘫痪，当局要求居民自行储存水和雨水。预计地区级灾难的最高紧急级别——国家三级紧急级别，至少将持续一百天。

有六层楼高的坎特伯里电视台大楼在地震中倒塌，仅存楼梯间。建筑中有电视台、一家诊所和一家英语语言学校——国王学校，该学校有来自日本、中国、菲律宾、泰国、沙特阿拉伯、韩国的留学生。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.starcanterbury.co.nz/local/news/christchurch-earthquake-heartbreaking-messages-fro/3942197/ |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2011-03-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724194402/http://www.starcanterbury.co.nz/local/news/christchurch-earthquake-heartbreaking-messages-fro/3942197/ |archivedate=2011-07-24 }}</ref>2月23日，警方认为废墟中人员无生还可能，遂停止[[搜救|搜救]]。建筑中死亡人数可能超过100人。当天夜里，灭火和恢复工作重新展开，<ref>http://www.stuff.co.nz/national/christchurch-earthquake/4692170/Christchurch-quake-toll-75-dozens-missing {{Wayback|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/national/christchurch-earthquake/4692170/Christchurch-quake-toll-75-dozens-missing |date=20171013214206 }} Accessed 24 February 2011 5:30 AM NZT</ref>之后日本派出的救援队加入。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.asahi.com/national/update/0222/TKY201102220563.html |title=「じしん」「息ができない」がれきの中から日本へメール |publisher=Asahi Shimbun |date=2010-02-22 |accessdate=2010-02-22 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110224071116/http://www.asahi.com/national/update/0222/TKY201102220563.html |archivedate=2011-02-24 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://search.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/nn20110222x2.html|title=Japanese feared trapped in rubble|publisher=The Japan Times|date= 2011-02-22 |accessdate= 2011-02-22}}</ref>

此次地震的地震波也造成200公里外西海岸[[庫克山国家公园|庫克山国家公园]]的[[塔斯曼冰川|塔斯曼冰川]]发生崩塌<ref>{{cite news|title=Earthquake caused glacier to crumble|url=http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/journal/earthquake-causes-glacier-to-carve-giant-chunk.htm|accessdate=2011-03-01|newspaper=australian geographic|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110302093954/http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/journal/earthquake-causes-glacier-to-carve-giant-chunk.htm|archivedate=2011-03-02}}</ref> 。

